Durban - A MINIBUS driver has been arrested for the accident that claimed the life of three people this morning on Dumisani Makhaye Drive. According to police spokesperson, Lt Colonel Thulani Zwane, the 33-year-old driver, who is at KwaMashu Police Station, faces three counts of culpable homicide and he is expected to appear at the Ntuzuma Magistrate's Court soon. The girls and another friend, aged between 13 and 14, had been crossing the road to get to their school when the vehicle collided with them. According to Rescue Care spokesperson, the teenage girls sustained major injuries and “there was nothing more paramedics could do for them.” The fourth girl, who sustained critical injuries, was treated on scene and rushed to a nearby hospital. Earlier this morning, Department of Education spokesperson Kwazi Mthethwa said the MEC Mthandeni Dlungwane had been “heavily heartbroken” by the news of the accident and would soon be visiting the families of the girls. POST